# =============================================================================
# Cygnus frontend — local development environment
# =============================================================================
# Copy to `.env` to override. The Vite dev server reads THIS directory's .env.
#
# IMPORTANT: the SPA itself reads NO VITE_* vars today. The API base is the
# same-origin `/api` path, which Vite proxies to the FastAPI dev server at
# http://127.0.0.1:8077 (hardcoded in vite.config.ts → server.proxy). So you
# normally do not need any frontend env to run `npm run dev`.
#
# This file exists to document the *local login bootstrap*: what backend to
# start, where the default admin credentials come from, and how to change them.
# (docs/HANDOFF.md §5 / §8.1.)
#
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 1. Start the backend (the FastAPI app now lives at cygnus.runtime.main)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
#   uvicorn cygnus.runtime.main:app --port 8077 --reload
#
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 2. Default admin credentials (seeded on first backend startup)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# The backend seeds an admin account on first run from its own settings
# (cygnus/runtime/config.py → Settings). The SPA never hardcodes these.
# Override them in the BACKEND's .env (repo root), NOT here — these lines are
# documentation only; the frontend ignores them.
#
#   DEFAULT_ADMIN_EMAIL=admin@cygnus.local
#   DEFAULT_ADMIN_PASSWORD=admin123        # ← change after first login
#
# Log in at /login with that email + password. The SPA stores the JWT bearer
# token in localStorage key `cygnus_token` (lib/authApi.ts) and sends it as
# `Authorization: Bearer <token>` on every /api call.
#
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 3. Auth endpoints the SPA depends on (same-origin /api)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
#   POST /api/auth/login   → { access_token, user }
#   GET  /api/auth/me      → current user (called on mount + refresh)
#
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# 4. If you must point the dev proxy at a different backend host/port
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Edit `server.proxy['/api'].target` in vite.config.ts directly — there is no
# env knob for it yet. (Add a `VITE_API_PROXY_TARGET` + use it in vite.config
# if you want this configurable; that would be a new feature, not a default.)
